data.title: Eleventh Street Bridge
data.text:
Creator

Pennsylvania Railroad

Date

September 4, 1917

Identifier

201203.1917.6509

Description

View looking west from the "US" Tower of the railroad bridge over Eleventh Street. The Fort Pitt Hotel is to the left of the bridge, the General Offices for the Pennsylvania Railroad Lines are in the middle background, with Voskamp's bakers' supplies shop on the right. This is one of a series of photographs taken to document the raising of Bridge No. 1 (Fort Wayne Railroad Bridge) by the Eastern Division of the Pennsylvania Railroad.
